  <title>Some basic concepts</title>
  <para>
    An organization communicates its purpose through mission and vision statements. These define an
    organization's scope and capabilities. The architecture must provide a suitable environment for
    an organization to realize it purpose. It provides a suitable infrastructure and defines
    suitable goals and strategies. The business processes which realize the services provided by the
    organization are deployed within the organization's architecture. They realize the stake
    holder's functional requirements for these services. 
  </para>
  
  <para>
    Before delving into organizational architecture and business process design, we first establish
    some core concepts forming the basis for the remainder of the material discussed in this book.
  </para>
  
